<item>
            <title>[PIG-3299] Provide support for LazyOutputFormat to avoid creating empty files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3299</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LazyOutputFormat (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-4927&quot; title=&quot;Part files on the output filesystem are created irrespective of whether the corresponding task has anything to write there&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-4927&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-4927&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) in hadoop is a wrapper to avoid creating part files if there is no records output. It would be good to add support for that by having a configuration in pig which wraps storeFunc.getOutputFormat() with LazyOutputFormat. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
