                            <comment id="13734079" author="wskemper" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2013 23:10:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Has anyone taken this on?  If not, it&apos;s something I&apos;d like to try.  It certainly bugs us!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13735232" author="rohini" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 21:21:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure. Go ahead and take a shot. I can work with you on the review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13862113" author="lbendig" created="Sat, 4 Jan 2014 01:16:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to address this issue with the patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13867181" author="daijy" created="Thu, 9 Jan 2014 22:28:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good. Would run all tests before commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13887109" author="dvryaboy" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2014 21:46:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt; shall we commit this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13887258" author="daijy" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2014 23:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for delay, let me kick off the tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13887271" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2014 00:01:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LazyOutputFormat is not in Pig bundled hadoop 1.0.0. We will also need to bump up hadoop version in order to compile. Let me give a try.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13887677" author="lbendig" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2014 12:01:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;, thank you for pointing this out. Which Hadoop version to upgrade? 1.0.1 has LazyOutputFormat.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13887970" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2014 18:32:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am testing against 1.0.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13888101" author="daijy" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2014 20:09:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Get TestHBaseStorage failure, but that even fail on trunk:&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;junit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Running org.apache.pig.test.TestHBaseStorage&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;junit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Tests run: 26, Failures: 5, Errors: 19, Time elapsed: 595.821 sec&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will open a separate Jira for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reattach patch with resync and upgrade to Hadoop 1.0.4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the patch will break users with old version of Hadoop. Can we make it not breaking them?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13888986" author="lbendig" created="Sun, 2 Feb 2014 17:43:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;, this modification is backward compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13889789" author="daijy" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 19:23:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resync with trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13889791" author="daijy" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 19:25:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Lorand!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
